      <div class="meal-card">
        <div class="meal-card-body">
          <div class="meal-card-tag">Breakfast · Option 1</div>
          <div class="meal-card-name">Greek Yogurt + 2 Eggs</div>
          <div class="meal-card-detail">1 cup plain Greek yogurt (18g) + 2 scrambled or hard-boiled eggs (14g)</div>
          <div class="meal-card-why">→ 90 seconds to assemble. The fastest 32 grams you'll eat all day.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="meal-card-protein">
          <div class="meal-card-grams">32g</div>
          <div class="meal-card-unit">protein</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="meal-card">
        <div class="meal-card-body">
          <div class="meal-card-tag">Breakfast · Option 2</div>
          <div class="meal-card-name">3-Egg Scramble + Cottage Cheese</div>
          <div class="meal-card-detail">3 eggs scrambled (21g) + ½ cup cottage cheese on the side (14g)</div>
          <div class="meal-card-why">→ Higher satiety than yogurt. Good if you train in the morning and need more fuel.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="meal-card-protein">
          <div class="meal-card-grams">35g</div>
          <div class="meal-card-unit">protein</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="meal-card">
        <div class="meal-card-body">
          <div class="meal-card-tag">Breakfast · Option 3</div>
          <div class="meal-card-name">Protein Shake + 2 Eggs</div>
          <div class="meal-card-detail">1 scoop whey protein (25g) + 2 hard-boiled eggs (14g)</div>
          <div class="meal-card-why">→ Zero cooking. Batch the eggs Sunday, shake takes 60 seconds. Best no-excuse option.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="meal-card-protein">
          <div class="meal-card-grams">39g</div>
          <div class="meal-card-unit">protein</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p><strong>Why breakfast matters most:</strong> After 40, your muscle's ability to use protein is blunted — a process called <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/anabolic-resistance-after-40/" style="color:var(--green-dark);">anabolic resistance</a>. Hitting 30+ grams at breakfast activates muscle protein synthesis early and sets the tone for the whole day. Miss it and you can't fully compensate later.</p>
    </div>

